wikipedia_page.main: William Bird (born 17 April 1795) was an English first-class cricketer associated with Cambridge Town Club who was active in the 1820s. He is recorded in two matches from 1821 to 1822, totalling 13 runs with a highest score of 8.

response: * Sir William Bird (lawyer) (1560/1–1624), lawyer and Member of Parliament for Oxford University
* Sir William Bird (solicitor) (1855–1950), British solicitor and banker, briefly a Conservative politician
